ce dollar cash payout option service in the Bank to receive their transfers this festive season. Ihekuna explained that Polaris Bank has existing relationship with all leading and licensed global money transfer operators, which makes it easy for Nigerians to receive money through the Polaris Bank. Polaris Bank has commenced payment of US dollars to all beneficiaries of money transfer across all its branches in Nigeria. According to a notice from Polaris Bank sent to its customers on Sunday, 6 December 2020, beneficiaries of money transfer can now receive their remittance in US dollars in cash… December 9, 2020 In "News" In an apparent move to boost dollar supply into the economy, the Central Bank of Nigeria (CBN) yesterday introduced new rules that allow beneficiaries of diaspora remittance and transfers into domiciliary accounts to receive their money in foreign currency. December 1, 2020 In "Money Market" New CBN rules allow beneficiaries to withdraw funds in USD to boost formal remittances to Nigeria WorldRemit, a leading digital cross-border payments business has announced that its customers in Nigeria can now receive remittances in foreign currency (USD) through its cash pick up providers. Following the announcement of the Central… December 4, 2020 In "News"